  <section class="page cover" id="cover">
    <div class="kicker">Genotwin · Board Briefing Pack · Q3 2026</div>
    <h1 class="cover-title">SAP SE</h1>
    <div class="cover-sub">Strategic decision intelligence &mdash; quarterly board record</div>
    <div class="cover-meta">
      <div><b>AEI Score</b> 3.42 · Band B · Above-Peer</div>
      <div><b>Prepared for</b> the Supervisory &amp; Executive Boards</div>
      <div><b>Issued</b> 28 September 2026 · Düsseldorf</div>
      <div><b>Record</b> AEI-SAP-Q3-2026 · confidential</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page" id="letter">
    <div class="kicker">I · Strategist letter</div>
    <h2>The quarter in one paragraph</h2>
    <div class="rule"></div>
    <div class="letter">
      <p>This quarter the AI-portfolio fragmentation pattern crossed the threshold where consolidation becomes the higher-value path. The genotype has been signalling this since Q1; in Q3 the cumulative unattributed spend and the peer movement together tip the decision. Two board decisions follow, with €520M of Year-1 value identified and conservatively estimated.</p>
      <p>The score moved from 3.35 to 3.42 over the quarter, driven by Capital Discipline as the Launchpad review advanced. We expect a further rise only if Decision 1 is executed before the FY close; absent it, the trajectory flattens.</p>
      <p>As always: every figure in this pack is read-only from your systems of record, cross-checked against the peer cohort, and traceable to source on the audit page.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="sign">Dr. Lena Fischer<small>Lead Strategist · Genotwin</small></div>
  </section>

  <section class="page" id="trajectory">
    <div class="kicker">II · Score trajectory</div>
    <h2>3.35 &rarr; 3.38 &rarr; 3.42</h2>
    <div class="rule"></div>
    <div class="traj">
      <svg class="traj-svg" viewBox="0 0 360 140" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <line x1="20" y1="120" x2="340" y2="120" stroke="#cabf9d"/>
        <line x1="20" y1="20" x2="20" y2="120" stroke="#cabf9d"/>
        <polyline points="60,86 180,74 300,62" fill="none" stroke="#9a7b2e" stroke-width="2"/>
        <circle cx="60" cy="86" r="4" fill="#9a7b2e"/><circle cx="180" cy="74" r="4" fill="#9a7b2e"/><circle cx="300" cy="62" r="5" fill="#7a2e2e"/>
        <text x="60" y="108" text-anchor="middle" font-family="JetBrains Mono" font-size="9" fill="#6b5d3a">Q1</text>
        <text x="180" y="108" text-anchor="middle" font-family="JetBrains Mono" font-size="9" fill="#6b5d3a">Q2</text>
        <text x="300" y="108" text-anchor="middle" font-family="JetBrains Mono" font-size="9" fill="#6b5d3a">Q3</text>
        <text x="60" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Fraunces" font-size="12" fill="#1a1610">3.35</text>
        <text x="180" y="66" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Fraunces" font-size="12" fill="#1a1610">3.38</text>
        <text x="300" y="52" text-anchor="middle" font-family="Fraunces" font-size="13" fill="#7a2e2e">3.42</text>
      </svg>
      <div class="traj-now">3.42<small>Band B · this quarter</small></div>
    </div>
    <p>Rising, peer-relative. The Capital Discipline dimension carried the quarter as the Launchpad consolidation review advanced from flagged to board-ready.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="page" id="d1">
    <div class="kicker">III · Board decision 1</div>
    <div class="decision">
      <div class="decision-tag">For decision · record AEI-SAP-DR-2026-027</div>
      <div class="decision-name">CONSOLIDATE <em>the AI portfolio</em></div>
      <div class="dgrid"><div class="dcell"><div class="dcell-v">€60M</div><div class="dcell-l">Year-1 release</div></div><div class="dcell"><div class="dcell-v">€2.1B</div><div class="dcell-l">Value at stake</div></div><div class="dcell"><div class="dcell-v">0.78</div><div class="dcell-l">Confidence</div></div></div>
      <p style="margin:0">Sunset the AI Launchpad track, absorb its differentiated capability into Joule, and resequence the Industry Cloud AI roadmap. Sunset path sits within Executive Board authority; legal timeline 90 days; no shareholder vote required.</p>
    </div>
    <ul class="timeline">
      <li><span class="date">Q1 2026</span><span>Fragmentation first flagged · 14 initiatives, 4 with overlapping IP claims.</span></li>
      <li><span class="date">Q2 2026</span><span>Launchpad identified as lowest-ROI bucket · €112M unattributed to revenue.</span></li>
      <li><span class="date">Q3 2026</span><span>Three peer consolidations confirmed · decision moves to board-ready.</span></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="page" id="d2">
    <div class="kicker">IV · Board decision 2</div>
    <div class="decision">
      <div class="decision-tag">For decision · record AEI-SAP-DR-2026-031</div>
      <div class="decision-name">ACQUIRE <em>customer-success capability</em></div>
      <div class="dgrid"><div class="dcell"><div class="dcell-v">€720M</div><div class="dcell-l">Indicative deal</div></div><div class="dcell"><div class="dcell-v">+1.4pt</div><div class="dcell-l">Net-retention lift</div></div><div class="dcell"><div class="dcell-v">0.66</div><div class="dcell-l">Confidence</div></div></div>
      <p style="margin:0">A bolt-on to close the post-sale success gap flagged by three cohort peers. The net-retention delta versus peers traces to post-sale, not product. Deal size sits within the standing M&amp;A mandate; board ratification only.</p>
    </div>
    <p>Sequencing note: Decision 1 should precede Decision 2 — the capital released by the Launchpad sunset substantially de-risks the acquisition envelope.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="page" id="blindspots">
    <div class="kicker">V · Blind-spot status</div>
    <h2>Three spots · dated &amp; valued</h2>
    <div class="rule"></div>
    <div class="bs">
      <span class="bs-status st-active">Active · decision pending</span>
      <div class="bs-head"><div class="bs-title">AI portfolio fragmentation</div><div class="bs-val">€2.1B at stake</div></div>
      <p style="margin:0">Fourteen initiatives competing for one budget owner. Addressed by Decision 1.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bs">
      <span class="bs-status st-watch">Watch · widening</span>
      <div class="bs-head"><div class="bs-title">Industry Cloud dilution</div><div class="bs-val">€680M</div></div>
      <p style="margin:0">Vertical sprawl weakening the core platform narrative; analyst fatigue rising.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bs">
      <span class="bs-status st-improving">Improving · absorbing</span>
      <div class="bs-head"><div class="bs-title">Acquisition integration drag</div><div class="bs-val">€3.6B exposure</div></div>
      <p style="margin:0">Absorption velocity improved two quarters running; now near peer benchmark.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page" id="peers">
    <div class="kicker">VI · Peer movement</div>
    <h2>Where the cohort moved</h2>
    <div class="rule"></div>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Cohort member</th><th style="text-align:right">Score</th><th>Quarter move</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><b>SAP SE</b></td><td class="n">3.42</td><td class="up">▲ +0.07</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Peer A</td><td class="n">3.44</td><td class="up">▲ +0.02</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Peer B (Oracle-class)</td><td class="n">3.20</td><td class="up">▲ +0.05 · consolidation booked</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Peer C</td><td class="n">3.05</td><td class="down">▼ −0.03</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>The cohort is consolidating around AI portfolios. SAP closing the gap to Peer A this quarter; Decision 1 would put it level or ahead.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="page" id="questions">
    <div class="kicker">VII · For the board</div>
    <h2>Four open questions</h2>
    <div class="rule"></div>
    <ol class="q">
      <li>Will the board ratify the Launchpad sunset before FY close, or defer one quarter?</li>
      <li>Is the €720M customer-success envelope within appetite given the Launchpad release?</li>
      <li>Should the Industry Cloud dilution be addressed now, or held until the consolidation lands?</li>
      <li>What governance does the board want over the next two AEI-logged decisions?</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="page" id="record">
    <div class="kicker">VIII · Institutional record</div>
    <h2>Eight decisions logged this quarter</h2>
    <div class="rule"></div>
    <div class="record">
      <div class="record-row"><span class="record-id">AEI-SAP-DR-2026-024</span><span class="record-d">Industry Cloud roadmap review · logged</span></div>
      <div class="record-row"><span class="record-id">AEI-SAP-DR-2026-025</span><span class="record-d">Joule resourcing confirmation · logged</span></div>
      <div class="record-row"><span class="record-id">AEI-SAP-DR-2026-026</span><span class="record-d">Capital reallocation framing · logged</span></div>
      <div class="record-row"><span class="record-id">AEI-SAP-DR-2026-027</span><span class="record-d">CONSOLIDATE the AI portfolio · for decision</span></div>
      <div class="record-row"><span class="record-id">AEI-SAP-DR-2026-028</span><span class="record-d">Peer-cohort reconstruction review · logged</span></div>
      <div class="record-row"><span class="record-id">AEI-SAP-DR-2026-029</span><span class="record-d">RESEQUENCE Industry Cloud · logged</span></div>
      <div class="record-row"><span class="record-id">AEI-SAP-DR-2026-030</span><span class="record-d">Integration-velocity checkpoint · logged</span></div>
      <div class="record-row"><span class="record-id">AEI-SAP-DR-2026-031</span><span class="record-d">ACQUIRE customer-success · for decision</span></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page" id="audit">
    <div class="kicker">IX · Audit &amp; reproducibility</div>
    <h2>How to check this pack</h2>
    <div class="rule"></div>
    <div class="audit">
      <b>Sources:</b> read-only from S/4HANA, Planview, Anaplan, Workday Adaptive + weekly public crawl.<br/>
